Kumail Nanjiani is a Pakistani-American comedian, actor, screenwriter, and podcast host who gained significant recognition for his role in the HBO comedy series "Silicon Valley" as Dinesh Chugtai. He has appeared in numerous television shows and movies since then.

Nanjiani was born on February 21, 1978, in Karachi, Pakistan. He later moved to the United States to attend Grinnell College in Iowa where he studied computer science and philosophy.

In addition to his acting career, Nanjiani has also found success working alongside fellow comedians through various stand-up comedy roles and worked as a writer/performer on Comedy Central's "The Meltdown with Jonah and Kumail."
